cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with the challenge of constructing a natural language interface to databases, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and database management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of SQL query logs to enhance the performance of NLIDBs, which falls under the category of database management, making cs.DB (Databases) another likely category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to map NLQs to database elements, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. The use of machine learning techniques to improve the performance of NLIDBs also makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. Finally, the paper involves experimental evaluation and performance analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category.
